   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SIX THE RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN THE WORKING SAINTS AND THE NEW WAY IN THE LORD'S RECOVERY Scripture Reading: 1 John 2:13-17; Phil 1:19-21a; Eph 4:12, 16; 2 Tim 4:7-8, 18b OUTLINE God's need in His economy today: The young and the middle-aged saints 1 John 2:13-17: Those believers who are grown-up in God's life.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Having overcome the evil one.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Being strong.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Having the word of God abiding within.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Loving not the world nor the things of the world.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Practicing the will of God.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The saints who are the fathers 1 John 2:13-14: Those believers who are mature in God's life.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Knowing the Christ who was before all things, who also is the Word of life who was there in the beginning 1 John 1:1.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Continuing to know this eternal Christ by the inner life until maturity.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The Lord's achievement in grace: In time and place.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>In circumstances.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>In grace.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>In the church.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>In the past, there being many men and few opportunities, whereas now, there being many opportunities and few men: The meetings and the service in the past not affording enough opportunity for the saints to serve: On the one hand, helping people to be regenerated and to grow.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>On the other hand, taking away peoples' opportunity to serve the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The meetings and the service today creating unlimited opportunities for the saints to serve: Opportunity abounding everywhere, from preaching the gospel by visitation, through the home meetings, to the small group meetings and the district meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Affording the saints the chance to let out a breath of life, which is their desire to serve the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Meeting the Lord's present need: By recalling the past experiences and vision.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>By responding to the Lord's attraction and calling.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>By renewing the former commitment and consecration.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>By setting aside one's time and specifically budgeting one's daily life.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>By fulfilling all the needs in the new way: Visiting people to preach the gospel and to gain new ones.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Regularly and consistently helping the new ones in the home meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Diligently learning to help the small group meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Seriously pursuing functioning and prophesying in the district meetings.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>A glorious living and a glorious goal: Living to live Christ Phil 1:19-21a.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>Goal to build up the Body of Christ Eph 4:12, 16.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>Result to receive the reward in the kingdom 2 Tim 4:7-8, 18b.</S>
   </TEXT>
